16/12/2019

Introduction

Atherosclerosis

Atherosclerosis: narrowing of the blood vessels through plaque formation

The Issue

  • Correlations between histological traits

  • Large datasets

  • Multivariate methods cannot handle large datasets

  • Current methods all (partly) univariate

The Solution

  • Latent variable method

  • Multivariate analysis and data reduction

  • Effect of individual mutations can be assessed

However‚Ä¶

  • P-value calculation computationally intensive
  • P-value estimation with bootstrapping untested

(P)O2PLS

  • (Probabilistic) Two-way Orthogonal Partial Least Squares
  • Assesses correlation between and within two datasets

The Objective

Estimation of p-values for PO2PLS using bootstrapping

Methods

The steps

  • Create simulation datasets

  • Assess bootstrapping methods

  • Use ‘best’ method to analysis dataset

  • Give biological interpretation of results
  • Test bootstrapping with different types of datasets

Questions?
